modules.description: Handles input/output interactions with processes by matching expected prompts using regular expressions and enforcing time limits on responses. Operates with strings, process handles, and timeout values. Used to automate responses in test scenarios where a program requires user input during execution.

Provides pattern and regular expression matching using PCRE for input streams. Works with strings, regular expressions, and custom match handlers. Used to detect specific file names or log patterns in interactive shell outputs.

Provides functions to match input against regular expressions using Str.regexp and handle expected patterns. Works with Expect.t and processes matches through custom callback functions. Used to detect specific text patterns in spawned process output, such as identifying filenames starting with a dot.

Provides functions to spawn, interact with, and monitor interactive processes. Works with process handles, regular expressions, and custom match functions to detect specific output patterns, end-of-file, or timeouts. Used to automate testing of command-line tools by sending input and verifying expected responses line by line.
